#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:18
msgid "What is the Linked Data Explorer?"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:20
msgid ""
"The **Linked Data Explorer** is a web application for discovering, "
"composing, and executing DMN decision model chains from Dutch government "
"knowledge graphs. It is built as part of the **Regels Overheid Nederland "
"(RONL)** initiative and connects directly to TriplyDB knowledge graphs and "
"the Operaton DMN execution engine."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:29
msgid "What it does"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:31
msgid ""
"The Linked Data Explorer lets you work with government decision models end-"
"to-end — from discovery to execution:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:33
msgid ""
"**Discover** available DMN decision models published to TriplyDB by "
"government agencies"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:34
msgid ""
"**Build chains** by drag-and-drop, connecting DMN outputs to DMN inputs "
"across agency boundaries"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:35
msgid ""
"**Execute chains** sequentially or as unified DRDs, with automatic variable "
"orchestration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:36
msgid ""
"**Query** any SPARQL endpoint with syntax highlighting and interactive graph "
"visualisation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:37
msgid ""
"**Model processes** with a BPMN 2.0 editor that links directly to DMN "
"decision models"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:38
msgid ""
"**Track governance** status: see which DMNs have been validated by competent "
"authorities"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:39
msgid "**Discover vendor implementations** of reference decision models"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:43
msgid "Ecosystem position"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:45
msgid ""
"The Linked Data Explorer is one of three components in the RONL ecosystem. "
"Understanding how they relate helps clarify why certain things work the way "
"they do."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:47
msgid ""
"graph TB\n"
"    CPSV[CPSV Editor<br/>cpsv-editor.open-regels.nl]\n"
"    LDE[Linked Data Explorer<br/>linkeddata.open-regels.nl]\n"
"    BACKEND[Shared Backend<br/>backend.linkeddata.open-regels.nl]\n"
"    TRIPLY[TriplyDB<br/>Knowledge Graph]\n"
"    OPERATON[Operaton<br/>DMN Engine]\n"
"\n"
"    CPSV -->|publishes TTL + DMN| TRIPLY\n"
"    LDE -->|discovers DMNs via SPARQL| TRIPLY\n"
"    LDE -->|executes decisions via REST| OPERATON\n"
"    LDE -->|API calls| BACKEND\n"
"    BACKEND -->|SPARQL| TRIPLY\n"
"    BACKEND -->|REST| OPERATON"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cindex.md:63
msgid ""
"The **CPSV Editor** produces the data — government service definitions and "
"DMN decision models published as Linked Data to TriplyDB. The **Linked Data "
"Explorer** consumes that data — discovering, chaining, and executing those "
"decisions. The **Shared Backend** handles orchestration logic that both "
"applications depend on."
msgstr ""

